1. First, check if the input array strs is null or empty. If so, return an empty string "".
2. Initialize a string variable prefix to the first string in the array: strs[0].
3. Loop through each string strs[i] in the array.
4. Inside the loop, use a while loop to check if the current string starts with the prefix. If not, shorten the prefix by removing the last character using Substring.
5. Once all strings have been processed, return the final prefix as the longest common prefix.